%N A395498 Number of derangements of [n] with 2 ascents.
%H A395498 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A395498/b395498.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%H A395498 <a href="/index/Rec#order_09">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (7,-13,-9,45,-15,-47,29,16,-12).
%F A395498 a(n) = A219836(n,n-3).
%F A395498 G.f.: 4 * x^4 * (1-x+x^2-3*x^3)/((1-x^2)^3 * (1-2*x)^2 * (1-3*x)).
%F A395498 a(n) = 7*a(n-1) - 13*a(n-2) - 9*a(n-3) + 45*a(n-4) - 15*a(n-5) - 47*a(n-6) + 29*a(n-7) + 16*a(n-8) - 12*a(n-9) for n > 8.
%e A395498 For n=4, the a(4) = 4 derangements are: [2, 3, 4, 1] (2<3, 3<4), [2, 4, 1, 3] (2<4, 1<3), [3, 4, 1, 2] (3<4, 1<2), and [4, 1, 2, 3] (1<2, 2<3).
%o A395498 (PARI) my(N=30, x='x+O('x^N)); concat([0, 0, 0, 0], Vec(4*x^4*(1-x+x^2-3*x^3)/((1-x^2)^3*(1-2*x)^2*(1-3*x))))
